Nigerian politician and pharmacist, Sam Ohuabunwa, has stated that he will not bribe Nigerians in order to get votes to win the presidential seat in 2023. The presidential aspirant on the platform of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) disclosed this while speaking to Punch, expressing that money may not play all the roles in the 2023 presidential election Ohuabunwa said, “I will not bribe anybody in this country. I will preach my message and let you and conscience to decide on what to do because I’m not coming to seek anything for myself. -Advertisement- “I’m coming to sacrifice myself, my comfort, my resources for the good of my country. So I don’t need to bribe people to do that sacrifice expect I’m looking for something else. “I believe that Nigerians are becoming wiser. Having gone round the country to talk to people, they are beginning to say we need somebody who has the right ideology, thinking, intelligence, vision competency, character and courage. “That is what I hear Nigerians saying, and money may not play all the roles in the 2023 presidential election.”